From: experintellia <280144245+experintellia@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Mon, 20 Jul 2026 01:19:55 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] web-app: read-aloud message action (browser TTS) behind an
 experimental setting

A "Read aloud" item in the message context menu speaks the message text
with the browser's built-in speechSynthesis -- fully local (OS voices),
no dependency, no network. While speech is playing the menu also offers
"Stop reading aloud". Closes #111 (slothfulchat-web).

Gated behind the new off-by-default `experimentalReadAloud` desktop
setting, mirroring `experimentalCompletionMenu` (patch 0050): one key in
DesktopSettingsType + getDefaultState(), one DesktopSettingsSwitch under
Settings -> Advanced -> Experimental features. The menu items are built
per right-click, so the speechSynthesis.speaking check for the stop item
is evaluated fresh each time. Utterances use the browser's default
voice/language; there is no API to detect a message's language.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
